
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `appstreamcli` baraye modiriat va didan metadata barname-ha dar format AppStream estefade mishavad. Shoma mitavanid etela'at raje' be barname-ha, nasakha-ye jadid, va description-haye anha ra az repository-haye software dar Linux begirid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `appstreamcli search [kalame]` --> 🔍 Jostojooye barname-ha ba estefade az kalame kelidi.
    🔹 `appstreamcli show [ID]` --> ℹ️ Namayesh etela'at kamel baraye yek barname ba ID moshakhas.
    🔹 `appstreamcli refresh` --> 🔄 Update kardane cache az repository-haye barname-ha.
    🔹 `appstreamcli validate [FILE]` --> ✅ Check kardane dorost boodane file AppStream XML.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ appstreamcli search firefox

    🔹 Jostojooye barname-haei ke "firefox" dar name ya description-e anha vojood darad.

    $ appstreamcli show org.mozilla.firefox

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at kamel baraye barname firefox.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ appstreamcli refresh

    🔹 Update kardane database AppStream az repository-haye software. In dastoor bayad ba hozoore root run shavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `appstreamcli` command is used to manage and view application metadata in the AppStream format. You can retrieve information about applications, updates, and descriptions from software repositories in Linux.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `appstreamcli search [term]` --> 🔍 Search for applications using a keyword.
    🔹 `appstreamcli show [ID]` --> ℹ️ Show detailed information for an application with a specific ID.
    🔹 `appstreamcli refresh` --> 🔄 Update the cache from the application repositories.
    🔹 `appstreamcli validate [FILE]` --> ✅ Check if an AppStream XML file is valid.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ appstreamcli search firefox

    🔹 Searches for applications that have "firefox" in their name or description.

    $ appstreamcli show org.mozilla.firefox

    🔹 Shows detailed information for the firefox application.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ appstreamcli refresh

    🔹 Updates the AppStream database from software repositories. This command usually needs to be run with root privileges.
